title: Chris Enahoro
text:
Chris Enahoro (born 7 April 1983) is an Australian former <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who played in the 2000s. He played for the <a href="South%20Sydney%20Rabbitohs">South Sydney Rabbitohs</a>. His position of choice was .
Playing career.
Enahoro as a youngster played in the South Sydney Juniors competition for <a href="Coogee%20Randwick%20Wombats">Coogee Randwick Wombats</a>. He made his first grade debut in his side's 62−22 loss to the <a href="Canberra%20Raiders">Canberra Raiders</a> at <a href="Canberra%20Stadium">Bruce Stadium</a> in round 26 of the 2004 season. Enahoro's only other first grade appearance came in his side's 36−12 loss to the <a href="Brisbane%20Broncos">Brisbane Broncos</a> at <a href="Lang%20Park">Lang Park</a> in round 12 of the 2005 season. He signed to play with the <a href="Gold%20Coast%20Titans">Gold Coast Titans</a> for the 2007 season, but did not make any first grade appearances for the club.
